{"author":{"id":"cc8322a500b8739c77faac347808f6026d9ccb7880d0aaa7ad76754163cd7fdb"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782568926,"nonce":"4Q8iSTZvsMiR0iMl4nnwTtCgnO4=","kind":"spec","title":"kref cranky-review remediation + help UX тАФ design"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782568926,"nonce":"QeUUW8ECErY8uPEaVVqXqTU3VJg=","body":"# kref cranky-review remediation + help UX тАФ design\n\n**Date:** 2026-06-18\n**Status:** approved (brainstorming тЖТ ready for implementation plan)\n**Scope:** the eleven findings in `.test-output/cranky-review-2026-06-18.md`\nplus a grouped/ordered `--help` layout.\n\n## 1. Context\n\nA cranky-user review of the current branch surfaced one P0, four P1, and six\nP2 findings. They split into behavior changes (observable CLI/JSON behavior),\ndocumentation drift, and polish. Separately, the maintainer asked for\nyargs-style command ordering/grouping in `--help` so common commands sit at the\ntop. This spec covers all of it as one remediation pass.\n\nThe command-alias feature (commits `4e5b47e`, `a8be240`) already landed,\nincluding an inline-alias `--help` template override in `cmd/kref/main.go`. The\ngrouping work here builds on that template and must keep aliases rendering\ninside groups.\n\n## 2. Goals / non-goals\n\n**Goals**\n\n- Close every finding in the review, or consciously reword the docs where the\n  behavior is acceptable but the prose was wrong.\n- Make `kref purge`'s default safe (no repo-wide object pruning unless asked).\n- Restore the documented reversibility of `kref rm`.\n- One consistent JSON key convention across all commands.\n- A grouped, intentionally-ordered `--help`.\n\n**Non-goals**\n\n- Building the deferred `.kref/` materialized-view feature (`kref checkout`). It\n  stays deferred; we only fix the README wording that implies it exists.\n- Cryptographic signing / encryption at rest (already documented limitations).\n- Making the repo public or tagging a release (out of our control here); we\n  only caveat the `go install` instructions.\n\n## 3. Decisions (locked during brainstorming)\n\n| Topic | Decision |\n|---|---|\n| P0 purge gc | gc becomes **opt-in**: default removes the ref only; `--gc` opts into `git gc --prune=now`. Replaces `--no-gc`. |\n| rm reversibility | **Ship `kref restore`** (un-tombstone op) + expose `kref list --include-deleted`. |\n| JSON casing | **snake_case** everywhere (json tags on `entry.Snapshot`). |\n| `--version` | **One line** (`kref \u003cversion\u003e`); `kref version` subcommand stays JSON. |\n| Help layout | **Grouped sections**, common groups first, alpha-sort disabled. |\n| Hook paths | Add a repeatable **`--ingest-path`** flag (default = today's four paths). |\n\n**Accepted breaking changes** (pre-release; recorded in CHANGELOG):\n`--no-gc` тЖТ `--gc`; `list`/`show` JSON key casing; `--version` output shape.\n\n## 4. Per-finding design\n\n### P0 тАФ `purge` gc is opt-in (`internal/store/store.go`, `cmd/kref/commands.go`)\n\n- `Store.Purge(id, gc, push)` keeps its signature; the CLI default for `gc`\n  flips from `true` to `false`.\n- `cmd/kref/commands.go` `newPurgeCmd`: remove `--no-gc`; add\n  `--gc` (\"also run repo-wide `git gc --prune=now` to excise objects now\").\n  `gc := flagGC` (no inversion).\n- `confirmPurge` already prints the repo-wide line when `gc` is true; keep that.\n  When `--force` **and** `--gc` are both set, print a one-line stderr warning\n  (`warning: running repo-wide 'git gc --prune=now'`) before purging, since the\n  prompt is skipped.\n- The fail-closed secret message (`internal/bridge/bridge.go:96-98`) changes its\n  remediation hint to `kref purge \u003cid\u003e --gc` so secret excision still gets the\n  immediate prune.\n- README delete table: `git gc --prune=now` is **repo-wide and only runs with\n  `--gc`**; default purge removes the ref and lets normal git gc reclaim objects\n  later. The \"Safe for secrets? Locally yes\" row applies to `--gc`.\n\n### P1 тАФ `kref restore` + `--include-deleted`\n\n- New op in `internal/entry/operations.go`: `Restore` (opcode after\n  `TombstoneOp`), `Apply` sets `s.Deleted = false` and bumps `UpdatedAt`. Add to\n  `operationUnmarshaler`. `NewRestore(author)` constructor mirroring\n  `NewTombstone`.\n- `Store.Restore(id)` mirrors `Store.Tombstone` (`store.go:167`): read across\n  tiers, append `NewRestore`, commit. Not-found тЖТ error.\n- `cmd/kref/commands.go`: `newRestoreCmd` (`restore \u003cid\u003e`, ExactArgs(1)), resolves\n  the id, calls `Store.Restore`, emits `{\"id\":тАж,\"status\":\"restored\"}`.\n- `newListCmd`: add `--include-deleted` (bool) тЖТ sets `ListFilter.IncludeDelete`\n  (store already honors it, `store.go:151`). Human output marks deleted rows\n  (e.g. a `(deleted)` suffix) so restore targets are visible.\n- README/help: `rm` description drops \"reversible\"; add a note that `rm` is a\n  reversible tombstone undone with `kref restore`, and `purge` is the irreversible\n  one. Delete table updated.\n\n### P1 тАФ snake_case JSON (`internal/entry/snapshot.go`)\n\n- Add `json:\"тАж\"` tags to `entry.Snapshot`: `id, kind, title, status, tier,\n  body, links, deleted, created_at, updated_at, created_by, created_by_email`.\n- `Link` struct: add matching snake_case tags.\n- Audit the hand-built maps so they already match (they do: `id`, `status`,\n  etc.). No casing change to `add`/`init`/`ingest`/`rm`/`purge`/`remote`/`sync`.\n- This makes `kref add` тЖТ `.id` and `kref show --json` тЖТ `.id` agree.\n\n### P1 тАФ `.kref/` README wording (`README.md` ingest section)\n\n- Rewrite the sentence at `README.md:112-113`. Storage is git refs\n  (`refs/kref-{private,personal,shared}/*`). `.kref/` is **reserved** for a deferred\n  materialized-view feature (`kref checkout`, see the design spec) and is\n  gitignored so that future feature never commits into code history. It is not\n  the current store and is not created today.\n- Keep `bridge.EnsureGitignore` writing `.kref/` (intentional forward-compat); its\n  comment already says \"synced via git refs, not the working tree\".\n\n### P1 тАФ `go install` caveat (`README.md` install section)\n\n- Lead with the working `task build` path. Mark the `go install\n  тАж@latest` snippet as available **once the repo is public and a release is\n  tagged** (the status line already notes it is unversioned). No code change.\n\n### P2 тАФ `--version` one-liner (`cmd/kref/main.go`)\n\n- Replace the JSON `SetVersionTemplate` with a one-line template\n  `kref {{.Version}}\\n` тЖТ renders `kref \u003cversion\u003e` (matches the approved preview).\n  `kref version` subcommand keeps JSON via `newVersionCmd`.\n- Update the existing spec in `cli_test.go` that asserts `--version` == `version`\n  to instead assert: `--version` is one line and parseable; `version` is JSON.\n- CHANGELOG note reverses the earlier \"`--version` now emits the same JSON\".\n\n### P2 тАФ post-trailer content absorbed (`internal/bridge/bridge.go`)\n\n- `splitMarker` currently returns `content[:marker]`, discarding everything\n  after the last trailer. Change it to strip **only the trailer line** (and its\n  adjacent blank line) and keep all other content, so text after the trailer is\n  treated as body. Re-stamp the trailer at true EOF via `withMarker`.\n- Net effect: appending a paragraph after the trailer and re-ingesting now\n  updates the entry with that paragraph (or stays `unchanged` only when content\n  is genuinely identical), instead of silently dropping it.\n- Idempotency holds: body is normalized to \"all content minus the trailer\n  line\"; re-stamping is deterministic.\n\n### P2 тАФ hooks `--ingest-path` (`internal/hooks/hooks.go`, `cmd/kref/commands.go`)\n\n- `hooks.Render` takes the ingest paths as a parameter (default\n  `[\"docs/superpowers/plans\", \"specs\", \".specify\", \"openspec\"]`) instead of\n  hardcoding them in the format string.\n- `newHooksCmd`: add a repeatable `--ingest-path` string slice flag on both\n  `install` and `print`; when empty, use the default set. The `post-commit`\n  hook's `files:` line is built from the flag values.\n- README hooks section documents the flag and the defaults.\n\n### P2 тАФ `list` short ids (`cmd/kref/commands.go`)\n\n- Human `list` prints a 12-hex-char short id (`it.ID[:12]`) in the first column;\n  `--json` keeps the full id. Resolve already accepts prefixes, so short ids are\n  directly usable with `show`/`rm`/`restore`/`purge`.\n- Width of the human column shrinks accordingly.\n\n### P2 тАФ lefthook banner placement (`internal/hooks/hooks.go`)\n\n- `Render` keeps the \"# Managed by `kref hooks install`\" banner. `Merge` strips a\n  leading managed-banner comment from the generated doc before folding, so a\n  merge into an existing `lefthook.yml` no longer strands the banner mid-file.\n  Fresh-file installs (empty existing) keep the banner at the top.\n\n### P2 тАФ `SECURITY.md` (new, repo root)\n\n- Sections: supported versions (pre-release; latest only), how to report a\n  vulnerability (contact), and a short trust-model sketch:\n  - Tiers as trust boundary: `private` never leaves the machine (structurally\n    unpushable); `personal`/`shared` reach configured remotes only.\n  - Ingest boundary: gitleaks scan quarantines/fails-closed on secrets.\n  - Known limitations (attribution is forgeable тАФ no signing; no encryption at\n    rest) framed as attacker тЖТ goal тЖТ current mitigation / residual risk.\n\n## 5. Help grouping (`cmd/kref/main.go`)\n\n- Set `cobra.EnableCommandSorting = false` in `newRootCmd` so add-order is\n  preserved.\n- Define groups and assign `GroupID`:\n  - `core` \"Core Commands:\" тАФ add, ingest, list, show\n  - `lifecycle` \"Lifecycle Commands:\" тАФ rm, restore, purge\n  - `sync` \"Sync Commands:\" тАФ remote, sync\n  - `setup` \"Setup Commands:\" тАФ init, hooks\n  - version тЖТ `additional` (or leave ungrouped тЖТ \"Additional Commands:\");\n    `SetHelpCommandGroupID`/`SetCompletionCommandGroupID` place the auto\n    commands under the same \"Additional\" group.\n- Add commands in the intended top-to-bottom order.\n- The existing inline-alias template override already rewrites the command line\n  in the grouped branch of the template, so aliases render inside each group.\n\n## 6. Testing\n\nTDD, redтЖТgreen, per item. New/changed specs (Ginkgo, in `cmd/kref` unless noted):\n\n- **purge default**: `kref purge --force \u003cid\u003e` (no `--gc`) removes the entry from\n  `list` and reports `\"gc\": false` in its JSON; `kref purge --force --gc \u003cid\u003e`\n  reports `\"gc\": true`. Update existing purge specs that pass `--no-gc` to drop\n  the flag (default) or use `--gc`.\n- **restore round-trip**: add тЖТ rm тЖТ `list` hides it тЖТ `list --include-deleted`\n  shows it тЖТ restore тЖТ `list` shows it again. (entry-level op test for\n  `Restore.Apply` in `internal/entry`.)\n- **JSON schema**: `kref add` `.id` and `kref show --json` `.id` both present;\n  `created_at` etc. present in `show --json`.\n- **--version**: one line, contains `kref` and the version, no `{`.\n- **post-trailer**: ingest, append a paragraph after the trailer, re-ingest тЖТ\n  entry body contains the paragraph; `action` is `updated`.\n- **hooks --ingest-path**: `hooks print --ingest-path foo --ingest-path bar`\n  emits a `files:` line referencing `foo bar`; default print unchanged.\n- **help grouping**: `--help` contains \"Core Commands:\", \"Lifecycle Commands:\",\n  and renders `add (new, create)` under Core.\n- **lefthook merge**: merge into an existing file does not place the managed\n  banner between user hooks.\n\nE2E (`test/e2e`): extend the lifecycle test to cover rm тЖТ restore.\n\n## 7. Rollout / sequencing\n\nEach finding (or tight group) is its own commit; `task check` green at every\ncheckpoint. Suggested order (low-risk doc fixes first, behavior last so tests\naccrete cleanly):\n\n1. Docs-only: `.kref/` wording, `go install` caveat, `SECURITY.md`.\n2. JSON snake_case tags (+ schema test).\n3. `--version` one-liner (+ test update).\n4. Help grouping/ordering (+ test).\n5. `list` short ids; lefthook banner; hooks `--ingest-path`.\n6. post-trailer absorption (+ test).\n7. `restore` op + command + `--include-deleted` (+ tests).\n8. purge gc opt-in (+ tests, message + README updates).\n\nCHANGELOG `[Unreleased]` gets Added (restore, `--include-deleted`,\n`--ingest-path`, SECURITY.md, grouped help), Changed (purge gc opt-in,\nsnake_case JSON, `--version` shape, `.kref/` wording), and Fixed (post-trailer\ncontent) entries. AGENTS.md gains a short note on the snake_case JSON convention\nand the grouped-help expectation for new commands."}]}